statements: SELECT * FROM user_behavior_analysis;
SELECT user_id, engagement_score FROM user_behavior_analysis ORDER BY engagement_score DESC;
SELECT user_id, interaction_datetime FROM user_behavior_analysis WHERE interaction_type = 'click';
SELECT AVG(engagement_score) AS average_engagement FROM user_behavior_analysis;
SELECT user_id, interaction_type, interaction_datetime FROM user_behavior_analysis ORDER BY interaction_datetime DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT user_id, interaction_type, interaction_datetime, engagement_score FROM user_behavior_analysis ORDER BY engagement_score DESC, interaction_datetime ASC LIMIT 10
SELECT * FROM user_behavior_analysis WHERE engagement_score > 50 ORDER BY interaction_datetime DESC LIMIT 5
SELECT user_id, engagement_score FROM user_behavior_analysis WHERE engagement_score BETWEEN 20 AND 50 ORDER BY user_id ASC
SELECT user_id, interaction_datetime FROM user_behavior_analysis WHERE interaction_datetime >= '2022-01-01' ORDER BY interaction_datetime ASC LIMIT 3
SELECT AVG(engagement_score) AS average_score, interaction_type FROM user_behavior_analysis GROUP BY interaction_type HAVING COUNT(*) > 1 ORDER BY average_score DESC LIMIT 5
SELECT * FROM interactions WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT engagement_type, engagement_score FROM engagement WHERE engagement_score > 50;
SELECT user_id, interaction_type FROM interactions WHERE interaction_timestamp > '2022-01-01';
SELECT * FROM interactions INNER JOIN engagement ON interactions.user_id = engagement.user_id;
SELECT * FROM interactions WHERE user_id = 1 ORDER BY interaction_timestamp DESC;
SELECT id, user_id, engagement_type FROM engagement WHERE engagement_score > 50 ORDER BY id;

SELECT user_id, preference_category, preference_value FROM user_preferences ORDER BY user_id ASC, preference_category DESC;
